args: What in the name of pennywhistles\nare you talking about?!
I believe I made myself clear.
I will be leaving the task of overseeing all\nProgenitor research at the Halidom to you.
You will be able to utilize such information\nin this fight ahead better than I ever could.
But you're still HERE. Why pass the\nresponsibility on to me now?
Just wait a few more days, dearie.\nI'll find a way to heal you.
No need. I have given up on fighting death.
Well, you may have given up, but I won't\njust sit back on my cozy davenport and\nwait for one of his heirs to die!
It is NOT well, you maddening man.
You will be undergoing treatment from\nChanzelia's medical corps, and that is\nthe end of the discussion.
Did you really expect me to do nothing\nafter hearing how your life hangs by the\nthinnest of threads?
I've gathered the world's finest doctors\nfrom North Grastaea, South Grastaea,\nTaiwu, and Hinomoto to aid you.
It is no exaggeration to say this team\nrepresents a gathering of the entire\nworld's medical expertise.
I remain as impressed as ever by your\ndiplomatic prowess, dear sister.

Oh, but we have more than just doctors:
my research division has been hard at
work creating the most technologically
advanced medical facilities ever seen.
Come with me to Chanzelia, Phares.\nGet treatment. Heal thyself.

While I am very much intrigued by this
medical corps you've assembled, I would
have you use it in the battle to come
instead of squandering it on me.
Did it ever occur to your stubborn brain\nthat you might be NEEDED in that battle?
I will have you aboard the Gran Fiore\nif I have to drag you there by force.
Oh, but this is not childishness, Brother.\nIt is a royal decree.
Your knowledge and wisdom will likely\nprove necessary in the times to come.
No matter how strong an army, it will\nalways lose without a sound strategy.\nI'm keeping you alive so we might win.
I see no reason why you cannot lead\nour army just as well as myself.

Because you have all the knowledge you've
accumulated in all your research, plus
memories from when the Progenitor was
using you as his vessel.
There are none better suited as a tactician\nfor this fight than you.
A ruler should be able to tell how best\nto utilize their own life, and you are\nnothing if not a ruler, Phares.
Your skill at masking emotion with logic\nhas greatly improved, little sister.
That sounds like projection to me,\nbig brother.
I do not argue based on emotion;\nI merely state objective facts.
Were it not for the Progenitor, I would be\ndead long since. The fact I still draw\nbreath is an aberration, nothing more.
Behold our current predicament if you\ndoubt me! This is what happened the\nlast time I tried to fight death.
I'm going to ask you something,\nand I need an honest answer.
Do you truly believe that dying a useless\ndeath serves as satisfactory atonement?
Is surrendering yourself to death honestly\nwhat you want?
I would hear your answer, Brother.
My apologies for the interruption,\nbut His Highness has just received\nan urgent message from Valkaheim.
Countless fiends and unidentified dragons\nhave descended upon Valkaheim.

The dragons are cloaked in massive
amounts of black mana, and powerful
though Prince Leonidas may be, this
fell horde threatens to overwhelm him.
Ah, I see. He seeks to hold them at bay\nin the hopes I know a way to deal with\nthe black mana that powers them.
Chelle, take me to the Gran Fiore.\nWe must make for Valkaheim! *cough*
*pant* *pant* Merely a flare-up—do not\ntrouble yourselves overmuch. Now please,\ntake me to Valkaheim with all speed!
Going to the front lines as you are now\nwould be suicide!
Who do you think more necessary for the\nupcoming battle: Leonidas or myself?
If I refuse to help Leonidas and the worst\ncomes to pass, our ability to stand against\nthe Progenitor would drastically weaken.
This fate must be avoided at all costs.\nWe NEED Leonidas in the battle to come.
You said yourself that a ruler is meant to\nknow how to utilize their own life, yes?
Leif, gather reinforcements to send to\nValkaheim. Cassandra, I leave the\nresearch team to you.
You've grown into a most strong woman,\nChelle, but your kind heart is the same as\nit has ever been.
...Do you think that's the sort of praise I\nwant to hear? Hmph.
Blast! It's just one after the other!
I came as quickly as I could, Leonidas.
And yet you still kept me waiting.\nBut where is our sister? You were aboard\nthe Gran Fiore, were you not?

She remained behind to manage the
defense of Chanzelia. If the worst comes
to pass and we fall here, the Radiant City
will be in danger as well.
I called you here to AVOID the worst\ncoming to pass.
Ah, yes. You wish me to solve your little\nblack mana situation, do you not?
Just lend me your wit, if naught else.\nWe cannot permit them to violate this land\nany more than they already have!
Of course. Let us deal with them at once!
